# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cottage Surgical (cottagedme) — environment variables
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values.
# `.env.local` is gitignored — never commit real credentials.
#
# Keys starting with VITE_ are bundled into the browser and are SAFE TO
# EXPOSE (the Supabase ANON key is RLS-protected). Keys WITHOUT the prefix
# are server-side only (migration scripts, edge functions) and must never
# reach the browser.
#
# NOTE: no Supabase project is provisioned yet. These are placeholders so
# the migration runner and (future) app know what to read.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Supabase (client-side) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# From: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ── Supabase (migrations only — NOT loaded by Vite) ───────────────────
# Full Postgres connection string used by scripts/run_migrations.py.
# Dashboard > Project Settings > Database > Connection string > URI (session pooler).
# Substitute [YOUR-PASSWORD] with the database password.
DB_CONNECTION=

# ── App public URL (server-side; powers auth redirects / invite links) ─
# Add ${APP_PUBLIC_URL}/set-password to Supabase > Auth > URL Configuration
# > Redirect URLs once auth is wired.
APP_PUBLIC_URL=

# ── Feature flags (client-side) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Internal tool: public self-serve signup stays OFF; users are invited by an
# admin. Leave UNSET to keep signup hidden; set true only if ever needed.
# VITE_SELF_SERVE_SIGNUP=
